{{refimprove|date=July 2015}} [[File:Exeter Dining Hall.JPG|thumb|View towards the High Table in the dining hall of [[Exeter College, Oxford]].]]
The '''High Table''' is a table for the use of [[fellow]]s (members of the [[Senior Common Room]]) and their guests at [[Oxford University|Oxford]], [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]], [[University of Dublin|Dublin]] and [[Durham University|Durham]] colleges. Other academic institutions (such as [[University of London]]; [[University of St Andrews]];<ref>[https://www.st-andrews.ac.uk/accommodation/ug/residences/stsalvators/ St Salvator's Hall]</ref> [[University of Manchester]] and [[University of Bristol]] in the UK, [[Queen's University]], and [[The University of Trinity College]] and [[Massey College]] at the [[University of Toronto]], and the [[University of Hong Kong]]) also have high tables. The table is normally at the end of the dining hall on a raised platform, although this is not always the case. On more formal evening occasions, [[dinner jacket]]s are worn. It is also normal to wear [[academic dress|academic gowns]]. [[File:S95HighTableFitzwilliam.jpg|250px|thumb|left|High Table in Dining Hall, [[Fitzwilliam College]], [[University of Cambridge]]]]
